Zambia to Borrow $167 Million to Buy Corn Crop, Post Reports

-- B y   A n t h o n y   M u k w i t a
-- 
2011-06-20T09:53:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-20/zambia-to-borrow-167-million-to-buy-corn-crop-post-reports.html
Zambia’s government plans to borrow
800 billion kwacha ($167 million) from local banks to buy the
country’s bumper corn crop, the Post newspaper reported, citing
Agriculture Minister Eustarckio Kazonga.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anthony Mukwita in Lusaka at 
